        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Fourth-instar larva of Anopheles barbirostris van der Wulp (modified from Townson et al., 2013). A, head, dorsal (left) and ventral (right) aspects of left side. B, thorax and abdominal segments I–VI, dorsal (left) and ventral (right) aspects of left side. C, abdominal segments VII, VIII, and X, left side. Abbreviations: A, antenna; C, cranium; P, prothorax; M, mesothorax; S, spiracular lobe; T, metathorax; I–VIII,X = abdominal segments I–VIII and X; 1–15 = setal numbers for specified areas, e.g. seta 5-C." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890720/files/figure.png" .

